metadata.Description.0.value: The Southeast ADA Center is one of ten regional centers in the United States that serves as a resource for individuals, businesses, and state and local governments by providing information, educational materials, and technical assistance for understanding, implementing, and adhering to the Americans with Disabilities Act (ADA).
